This document is an "IBM Batch Report" dated June 15, 2016, detailing the processing of 50 ballots (Ballot 1-50) for Batch Number 18 from the 'Bangor' Vote Collection Point (ID 2178) in New South Wales, related to Electoral Event ID 19694. The report provides metadata such as creation date (June 10, 2016) and operator details, alongside a comprehensive list of ballot-level checks. These checks include `QualityAssurance Checked`, `Initials Checked`, `Official Mark Checked`, `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Formality Result Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, and various `ATL` (Above The Line) and `BTL` (Below The Line) preference assessments (e.g., `ATL Preferences Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, `BTL Preferences Checked`, `BTL Mismatches`). For all 50 ballots in this specific batch, every listed check indicates "OK", signifying that no issues or anomalies were detected during their processing.

**Relevance to FOI Request:**
This document directly responds to Vanessa Teague's FOI request [LEX540] for "IBM Outputs" from 2016, specifically falling under the "IBM Batch Report" category. It provides granular data on ballot processing for a specific batch, aligned with the request's focus on batch metadata and ballot-level checks. While the FOI overview noted frequent "HAS ISSUES" entries, this particular report exclusively shows "OK" for all checks, including `UnusualMarkings Checked`, `Verification Action`, `Formality Reason Checked`, `ATL Mismatches`, and `BTL Mismatches`. This absence of issues contributes to the complete picture of ballot processing outcomes sought by the request, demonstrating instances of fully successful ballot processing.
